Function introduction, we are a public welfare organization concerned with mental health, initiated by students from Harvard, Columbia University, UCL, Fudan, Huazheng and other universities. We are committed to social innovation and youth power, to raise public awareness of mental health, promote the social integration of mental patients, promote the development of mental health in China, and ultimately achieve social inclusive and sustainable development.

Since the outbreak, we have heard on the Internet too many people with mental illness who are drug-free and seeking help. Infectious Diseases never affect everyone equally, and there are always groups and individuals, who are more affected and harmed in an epidemic, including our vast community of people with mental illness.

They face drug shortages due to community blockades and hospital closures, are further affected by negative news about the epidemic on the Internet, or are infected with a virus, but they face worse outcomes because of the bias against mental illness in the health care system.

For this issue of Ocean Wave FM, we've invited two community organizers of friends with mental illness, two psychiatrists, and a mental health social worker to talk about the plight of friends with mental illness in an epidemic.
